This paper discusses the use of Information-Centric Networking (ICN) to enhance the performance of CoAP, a protocol commonly used in the Internet of Things (IoT). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses security issues, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the benefits of ICN in terms of reducing communication overhead, which could place it in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) category. The paper also discusses the implementation of ICN in CoAP endpoints, which could place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of ICN to simplify implementation and reduce complexity, which could place it in the cs.DL (Digital Libraries) category.
